    "The acronym EDA most commonly stands for Exploratory Data Analysis, a crucial step in data science and statistics used to analyze and investigate datasets. It helps data professionals summarize main characteristics, spot anomalies, uncover hidden patterns, and test assumptions before applying machine learning or formal statistical models."
